<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbb5d535-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2000b–3"><num value="2000b–3">§ 2000b–3.</num><heading> “Complaint” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A complaint as used in this subchapter is a writing or document within the meaning of section 1001, title 18.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbb5d536-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/352/tIII/s304">Pub. L. 88–352, title III, § 304</ref>, <date date="1964-07-02">July 2, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/246">78 Stat. 246</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
